<br>
If I ever got 1 yellow in an hour, I would rip my hair out and either immediatly disband from one of the worst groups ever or think twice about my soloing abilities. 1 yellow is not good when even your regular pick up PoV group can get a full aa an hour. And yes that's 'pick up' and 'group' put together which yields that experience. Think of PoV as the new Velks or Dreadlands, but with actually good exp. And in Velk's I mean the groups tend to pick up the highest leveled people they can in their groups. So a level 65 mage will be picked up 95% of the time over a level 60 mage barring any huge problems. <br>
<br>
As for the Efreeti camp, is there any reason why you couldn't do it at level 65? Sure there won't be any exp but the loot is still there, not to mention you will be killing stuff faster. You can do 1 hour in PoV in a group + 1 hour doing Efreeti at 65 and still be way ahead exp wise then 2 hours doing Efreeti at 60.<br>
<br>
If it's a loot issue, you can farm a hell of a lot better at 65 then at 61, even without any new spells.<br>
<br>
I never understood the whole 'not leveling' thing. If it was the case why not just stay at level 12 to make sure that Blackburrow doesn't green out? Good thing AA exp is only allowed past 51 or else you would have level 12's trying to get aa's or trying to hold on to outdated exp spots.<br>
<br>
It's your choice not to level and I accept that, but don't try to pass it as if it is more advantageous or better exp<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . I think the level 65 mages are probably thanking you about not leveling so that they have less competition for group spots in PoP<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
