<br>
Doing efreeti at 65 when it is trivial would be boring.<br>
<br>
Some people look at their levelling as an adventure.  They experience each part of the game and get as much fun out of it as possible before moving on.<br>
<br>
It's like using the warp zones in Super Mario Brothers for the old NES.  You can beat the game by only doing levels 1-1, 1-2, 4-1, 8-1, 8-2, and 8-3 (I may have missed one).  That's 6-7 levels of the game when there are 24 total.  You see barely 1/3 of the content in the game if you use the warp zones.<br>
<br>
I mean, I'd hate sitting through 5 levels in The Overthere, never actually getting to experience what it was like to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">be</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> a mid-thirties magician.  It's the same reason I never even considered applying to the highest-end guilds on the server.  I'd have missed so much content.  &quot;Vindicator pwned!!!!&quot; the first time it happens is probably about equally exciting  as killing any mob in ToV for the first time... unless you've levelled to the point where Vindicator is a trivial fight.  Suppose you were to jump from a late kunark guild to a high velious guild.. You'd probably never even face Vindicator, and if you did, it'd be /yawn, /attack, /loot.<br>
<br>
IMO getting pasted by a mob a few times before you actually kill it makes the victory a whole lot sweeter, and for the most part it doesn't really matter at all what mob it is, so long as the reason you lose isn't because you're making tons of mistakes(that always sucks).  <br>
<br>
I'm in this game to have fun, and there's a lot more fun to be had than just getting stuff for your character.  You can just play Statbuilder if that's what you're looking for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=absolutemaster>Absolute Master</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(12/27/02 3:14:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=168.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://stuwww.kub.nl/~s338419/everquest/gohan.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoP Levels, a double edged sword.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's like using the warp zones in Super Mario Brothers for the old NES. You can beat the game by only doing levels 1-1, 1-2, 4-1, 8-1, 8-2, and 8-3 (I may have missed one). That's 6-7 levels of the game when there are 24 total. You see barely 1/3 of the content in the game if you use the warp zones.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
